						               													<description>Loud About is a fast-paced party game of &amp;ldquo;action memory&amp;rdquo; that will make you and your friends do and say wild and hilarious things. It&amp;rsquo;s ideal for both family parties and late-night shenanigans. Players must select actions and words to be loud about. The goal is to quickly ACT OUT and SHOUT OUT those actions and words faster than your opponents.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Loud About is a new twist on the classic kid&amp;rsquo;s game Menagerie from the UK.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In each round of Loud About, a Topic Card is drawn, for example &amp;ldquo;Dance Moves&amp;rdquo;. Everyone at the table then chooses a dance move and an action based on that dance move. The key is to remember everyone else&amp;rsquo;s dance move and action.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;On their turn, each player flips a card from the top of the deck, if the symbol matches with someone else card, a Face-Off occurs. In the Face-Off, the player who calls out and acts out the &amp;ldquo;dance move&amp;rdquo; of their opponent first, wins the card as a victory point. The player to collect the most victory cards wins the round.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;REVIEWS&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;ldquo;Your next favorite bar activity or party favor.&amp;rdquo;&amp;#10;&amp;ndash; Ryan Smith (Red Eye Chicago Tribune)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;ldquo;Like Anomia, a cafe favorite, but uses memory and personalization to make it unique! Something I would definitely recommend to customers.&amp;rdquo;&amp;#10;&amp;ndash; Christen Traviss (Snakes &amp;amp; Lattes)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;ldquo;If Snorta and Time&amp;rsquo;s Up had a secret love child, it might be this game.&amp;rdquo;&amp;#10;&amp;ndash; Stephen Conway (The Spiel)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;AWARDS&amp;#10;&amp;#10;- Tillywig 2017 TOP FUN Award Winner &amp;#10;http://www.tillywig.com/Toys-Games/Loud-About-A-Game-of-Action-Memory&amp;#10;&amp;#10;- Creative Child 2017 PREFERRED CHOICE Award Winner: Memory Kids Games Category&amp;#10;http://awards.creativechild.com/product/639-loud-about-&amp;#10;&amp;#10;- National Parenting Center 2017 SEAL OF APPROVAL Award Winner&amp;#10;http://the-parenting-center.com/loud-about-a-game-of-action-memory/&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
